statement.p:
Let \phi : G_1 \rightarrow G_2 be a homomorphism of groups. Then 




If e is the identity of G_1, then \phi( e) is the identity of G_2; 




For any element g \in G_1, \phi( g^{-1}) = [\phi( g )]^{- 1};



If H_1 is a subgroup of G_1, then \phi( H_1 ) is a subgroup of G_2;



If H_2 is a  subgroup of G_2, then \phi^{-1}(H_2) = \{ g \in G _1: \phi(g) \in H_2 \} is a subgroup of G_1. Furthermore, if H_2 is normal in G_2, then \phi^{-1}(H_2) is normal in G_1.

